Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.44,0:00:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I first became aware of myself in a coin locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.21,0:00:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In that eerie darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.02,0:00:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Blue...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.58,0:00:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The blue sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.56,0:00:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The blue ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.73,0:00:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.59,0:00:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The blue window frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.33,0:00:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go to Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.11,0:00:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Gunther Milch, arrested in 1988 for robbing an\Narmored car from the Bavarian BASF Bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.51,0:00:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Did time in Badenburg Prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.28,0:00:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Escaped in '91.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.32,0:00:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Spent half a year cutting through the iron bars...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.12,0:00:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with a nail sharpened into a file.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.02,0:00:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Was caught three days later...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.03,0:00:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and was sent to Kreiner Prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.36,0:01:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But in 1993...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.33,0:01:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,escaped through a drainage pipe in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.53,0:01:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The prison uniform, soaked with excrement, was\Nfound three days later on a nearby riverbank.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.40,0:01:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrested for attempted robbery of a Maximilian\N& Co. paycheck delivery truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.17,0:01:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In '97, escaped from a shower stall in Ingeburg Prison...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.81,0:01:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,after spending a year, and a half\Ndigging a hole with a spoon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.65,0:01:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The toilet here stinks pretty bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.12,0:01:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I escaped through a sewer once, so I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.62,0:01:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up and walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.23,0:01:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What a gloomy look.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.20,0:01:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Face forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.40,0:01:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm not mistaken, that's Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.97,0:01:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep walking!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.14,0:01:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think he'd look so depressed and hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.80,0:03:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask you one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.84,0:03:27.28,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(750,600)\pos(360,340)}The Lawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.81,0:03:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In '86, the poisonings at Eisler Memorial\Nof Director Heinemann...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.41,0:03:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Surgical Director Oppenheim, and Dr. Boyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still deny any involvement?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.09,0:03:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we started the interrogation,\Nyou haven't said a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.83,0:03:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.26,0:03:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma, what are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.57,0:03:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you keep silent, you'll still be\Nprosecuted and made to stand trial...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.24,0:03:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and you won't stand a chance in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.31,0:03:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.67,0:04:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell us everything and remove the\Nburden from your shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.25,0:04:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.15,0:04:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the commotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.28,0:04:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Milch has stomach problems!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.49,0:04:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Dürer!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.59,0:04:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Dr. Dürer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.33,0:04:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor's currently in the interrogation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.63,0:04:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter drank some sort of cleaning fluid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.37,0:04:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he choking on his own vomit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.27,0:04:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.28,0:04:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.34,0:04:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't breathe...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.91,0:04:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.31,0:04:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we'll have to use him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.65,0:04:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.29,0:04:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Please have a look at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.63,0:04:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it hurt here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.31,0:05:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring some hot water...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.71,0:05:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a towel, and a change of clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.68,0:05:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.28,0:05:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be contagious!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.65,0:05:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you pretending to be sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.56,0:05:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Show some mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.43,0:05:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the first doctor to see through my act so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.13,0:05:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh, I figured that if I got sent to the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.77,0:05:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have a better chance of escaping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.84,0:05:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how I rob armored cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.55,0:05:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I jump out in front of the truck and pretend to be sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.48,0:05:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When the guards run out of the truck to help me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.95,0:05:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,my accomplices show up with guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.76,0:05:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never killed anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.29,0:05:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.03,0:06:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.40,0:06:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna escape with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.10,0:06:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a gloomy-looking face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.81,0:06:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying in a place like this will suck the life out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.04,0:06:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate cramped places the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.75,0:06:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I first became aware of myself in a coin locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.15,0:06:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In that eerie darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.72,0:06:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When my parents went to work, they put me\Nin there and I'd eagerly await their return.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.73,0:06:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let's go to Tunisia someday."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.27,0:06:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents used to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.17,0:06:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad said...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.51,0:06:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"If work goes well today, let's go to Tunisia."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.11,0:06:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But I waited for three days, and\Nthey never came back for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.49,0:07:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents must have left me behind\Nand went to Tunisia on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.19,0:07:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.16,0:07:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get out of this cramped place...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.53,0:07:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and go to Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.34,0:07:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What a gloomy-looking face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.31,0:07:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no hope in your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.38,0:07:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Not like mine, where hope exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.41,0:07:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do if they catch you again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.92,0:07:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just escape again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.69,0:07:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times it takes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.79,0:07:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.53,0:07:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to say nothing again today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.96,0:07:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.77,0:07:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,even as we speak, something terrible is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.77,0:07:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to hear the truth quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.44,0:07:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But you won't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.84,0:07:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't believe a word I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.61,0:07:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.72,0:08:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.45,0:08:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.49,0:08:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.89,0:08:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.89,0:08:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I sentence the accused to twenty years in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.03,0:08:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When my dad was found guilty...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.37,0:08:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,my path in life was decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.47,0:08:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,After the war...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.64,0:08:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,my dad moved from Sudeten,\NCzechoslovakia, to Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.41,0:08:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,where he opened a small radio station in 1949.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.44,0:08:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,However, during the cold war between\NEast and West Germany in the 60s...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.45,0:08:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he was arrested for being a spy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.38,0:08:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the murder of a Bundestag member's secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.92,0:08:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,His arrest was a huge shock to the West German society.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.69,0:08:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad pleaded innocent...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.69,0:08:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but was still sentenced to twenty years in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.40,0:08:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom continued to proclaim my dad's innocence...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.37,0:08:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,until she died in '71.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.47,0:08:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad died in prison in '72, filled with resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.01,0:09:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In '73, while I was in high school...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.21,0:09:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,my dad's innocence was proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.95,0:09:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,After I graduated from Düsseldorf University...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.65,0:09:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a job at the Hoffmann law firm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.08,0:09:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a major firm at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.35,0:09:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I won my first case...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.92,0:09:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,proving the charges were false\Nand the defendant was innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.49,0:09:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, I consistently won a not-guilty\Nverdict in every case I argued.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.40,0:09:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Fritz Verdeman...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.77,0:09:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,went from being the son of a spy, to\Na "star" in the legal world, overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.94,0:09:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"Somewhere Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.91,0:09:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The radio station my dad managed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.65,0:09:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,started and ended each day with this song.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.12,0:09:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To people like you who lived in the East...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.62,0:09:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,this song may seem like a symbol of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.63,0:09:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.36,0:09:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad died in prison while asserting his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.57,0:09:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to let him rest in peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.80,0:10:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to take on every case in which...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.80,0:10:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a possibility that the defendant\Nmay actually be innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.87,0:10:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me more...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.41,0:10:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about Dr. Tenma's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.65,0:10:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Elsa, how'd your checkup at the maternity center go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.96,0:10:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It went very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They said I could expect the baby any day now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.83,0:10:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You just passed a man in the lobby, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.60,0:10:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.77,0:10:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he the one you mentioned before?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.27,0:10:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.10,0:10:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Alfred Baul...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked me to represent Dr. Tenma with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.38,0:10:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you turn down Dr. Tenma's case the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.45,0:10:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, because the client at the time\Nwas Hans Georg Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.72,0:10:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know why a billionaire would\Nwant me to defend Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.22,0:10:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time, the reason is clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What reason would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.76,0:11:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The clients who brought the case to Baul were...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.27,0:11:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the patients whose lives were saved by Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.11,0:11:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This much is certain...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.58,0:11:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma was an outstanding doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.91,0:11:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you take the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.91,0:11:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If I won the case, the billionaire\Nwould pay me handsomely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.29,0:11:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But not so with the patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.22,0:11:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were working solely for profit...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.09,0:11:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd have a bigger office by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.10,0:11:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.17,0:11:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is "Somewhere Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.45,0:11:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.75,0:11:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.95,0:11:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.49,0:12:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That aside, let's go get something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.53,0:12:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,For the new life that's about to be born...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.16,0:12:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to eat enough for two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.47,0:12:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.07,0:12:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The baby's kicking because it's hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.04,0:12:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, honey, which restaurant would you like to go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.71,0:12:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How about that one place?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.75,0:12:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,disappeared in the midst of the blaze.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.09,0:12:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the last time...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.89,0:12:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.29,0:12:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I start from the beginning again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.36,0:12:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll repeat it as many times as I have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.23,0:12:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,As many times... as the truth takes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.04,0:12:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the fourth one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.61,0:12:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The lawyers who wanted to represent\Nme in court all suggested...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.98,0:12:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that I plead guilty to some of the charges...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.91,0:12:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to lighten my sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.95,0:13:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all they could talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.18,0:13:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.05,0:13:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me that you don't really care\Nabout proving your innocence...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.96,0:13:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,rather, you want to prove the existence\Nof a certain young man named Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.19,0:13:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.00,0:13:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, you don't need a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.67,0:13:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.67,0:13:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When did all of this {\i1}really{\i} begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.77,0:13:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, when a boy who was shot\Nin the head was brought in...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.28,0:13:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, did anything happen before that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.19,0:13:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A Turkish woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.16,0:13:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Give my husband back!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.09,0:13:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}People's lives aren't equal.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.40,0:13:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's lives are equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.17,0:13:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.37,0:13:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,if I made the right decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.38,0:14:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell if a patient is good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.24,0:14:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My crime was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.35,0:14:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My crime was saving that boy's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.25,0:14:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.12,0:14:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.99,0:14:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Does a doctor have the right to choose to save a life...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.29,0:14:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,based on whether the patient is good or evil?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.09,0:14:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Lives aren't equal.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.40,0:14:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.57,0:14:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.17,0:14:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, I can't decide...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.00,0:14:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same way with lawyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.04,0:14:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know if the people we defend are good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.91,0:14:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is the list of people who asked me to represent you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.12,0:14:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Michael Hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.89,0:14:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Stefan Kramp.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.82,0:14:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Franz Kiefer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.39,0:14:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Rudolf Huber.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.33,0:14:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Kiefer...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.69,0:14:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Huber...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.10,0:14:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They're doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.43,0:14:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Horst Henschel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.37,0:14:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Arnold Hoss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.77,0:15:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hoss, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.40,0:15:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right... I wonder if he's living\Nhappily with his grandkids?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.04,0:15:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Time's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.08,0:15:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.68,0:15:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.28,0:15:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.32,0:15:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.59,0:15:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I will represent you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.92,0:15:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Lawyers can't tell if a person is good or evil, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.79,0:15:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When we represent someone, there's\Nonly one thing we can do...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.80,0:15:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Have faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.24,0:15:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,One more glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.17,0:15:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I said one more!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.28,0:15:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But, ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Since when did this bar start refusing to serve customers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.19,0:15:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.29,0:15:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You just laughed at me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.33,0:16:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.26,0:16:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You did!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.76,0:16:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You looked at me and laughed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.93,0:16:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.40,0:16:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.37,0:16:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,used to come to my house to kiss ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.24,0:16:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the assistant manager at Nordrhein-West Bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.71,0:16:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with that look?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.11,0:16:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,After going to the trouble of coming back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.78,0:16:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva Heinemann has returned to Düsseldorf!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.96,0:16:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for filling me in on these important details...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.19,0:16:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.70,0:16:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as I heard you were going\Nto be Dr. Tenma's lawyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.53,0:16:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I started trying to get in touch with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.33,0:16:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize for being difficult to reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.57,0:16:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been all over the place asking about the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.01,0:16:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Asking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.04,0:16:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, asking Dr. Tenma's supporters, his former patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.51,0:16:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.61,0:16:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma seems to be an outstanding doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.75,0:16:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.85,0:16:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,did you get any important evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.05,0:17:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.46,0:17:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hoping to find a witness to confirm Dr. Tenma's alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.33,0:17:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, if we want to prove Tenma's innocence...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.00,0:17:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to be able to prove that\Nthis Johan person actually exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.47,0:17:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.94,0:17:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.10,0:17:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,About Dr. Tenma attempting to\Nshoot this young man, Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.51,0:17:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to withhold that part of your testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.08,0:17:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.84,0:17:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But... that's the only event that proves Johan exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.68,0:17:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether or not Johan exists, Tenma is still innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.25,0:17:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hear me out, Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.02,0:17:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All this country wants is a scapegoat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My child will be born soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.93,0:17:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,For my unborn child's sake, I want true justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.93,0:17:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The judges and prosecutors who want an easy solution...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.37,0:17:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have groundlessly sentenced innocent people\Nfor crimes they never committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.08,0:17:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Our unjust country must repent for its sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.61,0:18:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what's important, Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.65,0:18:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for a particular person right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.69,0:18:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.12,0:18:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She may know something vital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.90,0:18:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.85,0:18:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.33,0:18:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma's former fiancée...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.77,0:18:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.40,0:18:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong, Dr. Reichwein?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.67,0:18:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,She's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.61,0:18:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She came with me to this city...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.91,0:18:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.12,0:18:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all laughing... Everyone is laughing at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.46,0:18:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They take one look at me and laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.99,0:18:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva, about what I said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.33,0:18:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm listening!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.73,0:18:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.86,0:18:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Please meet with the lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.03,0:18:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,For Tenma's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.00,0:18:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.20,0:18:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you before, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.07,0:18:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.41,0:19:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,actually tried to shoot him, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.11,0:19:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised when you first told me about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.12,0:19:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But you didn't shoot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.52,0:19:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, I didn't shoot...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.32,0:19:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.72,0:19:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it would've been a problem if he died!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.76,0:19:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let the man who ruined my life die that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.43,0:19:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I want him to rot in prison for the rest of his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.97,0:19:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,forever regretting that he dumped me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.49,0:19:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.95,0:20:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened? Did you have a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.59,0:20:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard... three gunshots...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.49,0:20:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.36,0:20:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't see him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.56,0:20:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The blonde boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.97,0:20:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.33,0:20:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Have...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.40,0:20:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you seen Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.61,0:20:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"Somewhere Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.81,0:20:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A symbol of freedom...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.68,0:20:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdeman, your wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.65,0:20:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She's gone into labor, and she was\Ntaken to the maternity center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.52,0:20:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.59,0:20:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. klinger, call Mr. Baul immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.79,0:20:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.89,0:21:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Please ask him to meet with Dr. Tenma in my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.60,0:21:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.80,0:21:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm your lawyer, Baul.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.27,0:21:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I was asked to meet with you today...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.84,0:21:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you doing? Getting enough sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.01,0:21:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.11,0:21:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.74,0:21:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.81,0:21:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was originally right-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.68,0:21:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get used to holding a pen with my left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.56,0:21:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,My right hand won't move anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.56,0:21:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.46,0:21:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have lost quite a bit of weight...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.03,0:21:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, I impressed even myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.04,0:21:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when I escaped that sea of fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.78,0:21:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You actually shot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.93,0:22:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.13,0:22:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,may not be used to holding a pen\Nbut it can handle a gun just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.37,0:22:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.84,0:22:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking of killing someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.24,0:22:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Your former fiancée...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.04,0:22:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva Heinemann.
